President Obama and Italian Prime Minister Renzi held a joint press conference at the White House to discuss a range of issues, including economic growth, security, and the refugee crisis. President Obama commended Italy for its strong alliance with the United States and its contributions to the coalition against ISIS. He also expressed support for Italy's economic reforms and its efforts to stabilize Libya. Prime Minister Renzi emphasized the importance of a united Europe and called for greater investment in Africa to address the root causes of migration. The leaders also discussed the ongoing offensive against ISIS in Mosul and the need for a coordinated response to the refugee crisis. President Obama criticized Donald Trump's claim that the election is rigged and called on him to accept the results and work for a smooth transition of power if he loses.